terms.term: North Declination is the correction applied based on the year and location of magnetic north measurement to convert to True North or geodetic North. Because the Magnetic North pole in moving with the magnetic fields of the Earth, a calculation to True North is computed overtime and location of observation of Magnetic North.

Is based on a defined Geodetic Datum that is repersented by a Spheroid or Ellipsoid model. Provided in Latitude, Longitude (Decimal Degrees or Sexidecimal) with height above or below the ellipsoid is the angular coordinate system. A 3D Geocentric X, Y, & Z in meters is also possible.

The geoid is gravity model. Gravity at the sea level is similar globally. As one increases in elevation gravity changes. Therefore; gravity can be used to determine your elevation above sea level. Geoid models have been built regionally in reference to that regions Vertical Datum. It is important that you are using the proper regional Geoid Model.

2D Projected plane, grid, on Ellipsoid/Geodetic Datum. Projection method reduces distortion in (i)distance, (ii)direction, or (iii)area. Coordinates are provided in either a X, Y or Easting, Northing value with units of Metres or USFeet.

True Geodetic North is defined with an ellipsoid origin at the North Pole. Astronomical north is closely related to True North. Magnetic North (constantly varying) differs from True by a Declination observation.
